translated: Öster, Anders Emanuel, former mayor, Söderköping, born on October 19, 1888, in N. Finnskoga, Värmland County, the first child of landowner Jan Ö. and Sara Jonsson. Married on March 23, 19xx, to Karin Rosén. Graduated from Karlstad University in 1906, completed a law degree at Uppsala University in 1917. Became mayor of Söderköping in 1923. Served as chairman of the board for the savings bank, for the Östergötland Private Bank branch in Söderköping, and for the local secondary school in Söderköping. Vice chairman of the board for the Norrköping-Söderköping-Vikbolandet Railway Company since 1937. Awarded the Royal Order of Vasa in 1941.
